title: From John O'Groats to Land's End; Or, 1372 miles on foot; A book of days and chronicle of adventures by two pedestrians on tour
author: Naylor, John Anderton
snippet: The Minto estate adjoined Hassenden, and the country around it was verybeautiful, embracing the Minto Hills or Crags, Minto House, and a castlerejoicing, as we thought, in the queer name of "Fatlips."
